feedbackview.title: Support
feedbackview.content:
FAQ

How does this work?

Every day, Hinge provides you with a batch of potentials - people we think would be good matches for you. A lot goes into figuring out who's best for you. First and foremost, Hinge considers social proximity (i.e. the friends you have in common). But we also take into account education level, interests and popularity. For each potential match, anonymously choose to either pass or favorite. If you favorite someone, you'll appear as a potential in their queue, and if they favorite you as well, Hinge provides an introduction via chat.

How do I get in touch with my matches?

Whenever there's a match, Hinge opens a chat. You can access these chats by hitting the "heart" icon at the top right of the app.

Why friends of friends?

Because social proximity is the best indicator of how compatible someone is. After all, most people still meet through their friends. We feel having a friend in common is more relevant than geolocation or whatever random stuff people happen to put on their dating site profiles.

Can I choose who I see?

Yes! You have total control over your match filters in terms of age and geography. You can select these options in the Preferences section of the app.

Can I go back if I pass on someone?

If you pass on someone, you may go back one person for a "redo". Otherwise, they're gone - for now. Look for our "Double Check" feature coming soon!

How do I edit my profile?

Just go to "My Profile" to edit and preview your profile. Right now you can edit ethnicity, religion, height, preferred date spots and personality tags. To keep the experience authentic for all users, we use your Facebook information for work, education history etc. Please note that our photo selector is still in the works, so currently the 25 most recent photos from your Profile Pictures album on Facebook will appear to other Hinge users.

How do I remove the app?

To remove the app, click https://facebook.com/appcenter/my from a desktop computer (will not work from mobile device) and remove the app from the list. Then, on your phone, delete the app icon as you normally would.

How do I log out of the app?

Simply click the button below. NOTE: You will need to "force close" Hinge before you can use it again.
